# Localization

- Always localize new user-facing UI copy.
- Use the existing i18n helpers in `web/src/lib/i18n.ts` and `web/src/lib/i18n-server.ts`.
- Add both English (`en`) and Portuguese (`pt`) strings for any new translation key.
- Prefer passing the current `locale` into shared components instead of hardcoding English text.
- Keep dynamic text using `t(locale, "key", { value })` placeholders rather than string concatenation when the sentence structure may differ by language.
- Do not add new hardcoded labels, button text, empty states, headings, placeholders, or aria labels without considering localization.
